<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 4:28PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Moore, northwestern
Harnett, eastern Montgomery, north central Richmond, southeastern
Randolph, Lee, southwestern Wake and southern Chatham Counties
through 530 PM EDT...
At 427 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms 11
miles southeast of North Carolina Zoo, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Cary, Sanford, Southern Pines, Pittsboro, Carthage, Fuquay-Varina,
Pinehurst, Biscoe, Goldston and Seagrove.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM EDT for
central North Carolina.</instruction>
